glosses: to arrive; to reach a location
to reach a stage or a state of being

examples.translation: I couldn't reach, I couldn't get enough of its smell, its taste

glosses: used to challenge or encourage someone

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish وارمق (varmak), from Proto-Turkic *bar- (“to walk, go; to come, reach”). Cognate of Old Turkic [script needed] (bar-), Azerbaijani varmaq, Uzbek bormoq etc.
